# StreamList project rules

1. All API calls must go through `src/api/client.ts` only. Never import Axios directly in any hook or component.
2. All color values must come from `src/theme/colors.ts`. No hardcoded hex strings anywhere in component or screen files.
3. All spacing values must come from `src/theme/spacing.ts`. No hardcoded pixel numbers in StyleSheet files.
4. Every screen must fetch data exclusively through a custom hook. No inline `useEffect` + `fetch` or `useEffect` + `axios` inside screen components.
5. Every custom data-fetching hook for a **single** remote resource must expose `{ data, loading, error, refetch }`. TMDB paginated movie lists may additionally expose `loadMore` and `hasMore` (see `usePaginatedMovieList`). Composite hooks such as `useHome` compose those resources: each async slice (`genres`, `trending`, `topRated`, `genreMovies`) follows `AsyncResource` or `PaginatedMovieListResource`, and screen-specific UI state (for example `selectedGenreId`) may appear alongside those slices.
6. No `any` types anywhere. TypeScript strict mode is enforced.
7. No third-party UI component libraries. No React Native Paper, Elements, or similar.
8. No CSS-in-JS. No NativeWind, Styled Components, or similar.
9. No navigation library other than React Navigation v6.
10. No state management library other than Zustand.
11. Never use a 1px solid border at full opacity. Boundaries are created through background color shifts or spacing only.
12. Never hardcode the TMDB API token in any source file. It must come from environment variables only.
13. All navigation params must be typed using the interfaces in `src/navigation/types.ts`. No untyped `navigation.navigate()` calls.
14. No Redux, MobX, or any state library other than Zustand.
15. StyleSheet.create() only for styling. No inline style objects except for dynamic values.
16. Never use ScrollView for content rows that need infinite scroll. Always use FlatList for horizontal movie/content rows.
17. Genre selection state must always stay inside the useHome hook as local component state. Never put genre selection in Zustand store.
18. Never hardcode any hex color value in any component, screen, or hook file. Every color must be imported from src/theme/colors.ts.
19. Never hardcode any spacing or pixel value in StyleSheet. Every spacing value must come from src/theme/spacing.ts.
20. ContentCard must always handle null poster_path gracefully by showing a dark placeholder. Never pass a null or undefined source to an Image component.
21. Every FlatList content row must implement onEndReached for infinite scroll with onEndReachedThreshold={0.3}.
22. Every async section must show SkeletonCard components while loading — never use ActivityIndicator or spinner for content rows.
23. Never cancel a previous API call by ignoring the response silently. Use a ref-based isMounted check or track the current genreId to prevent stale state updates.
24. All navigation.navigate() calls must use fully typed params from src/navigation/types.ts. Never pass untyped route params.
25. DetailScreen must never show the bottom tab bar. It is a stack screen pushed over the tabs.
